      </task>
      <task> <p>Compare what you got in part <m>a</m> with the values you found in the previous activity. What do you notice? </p>
      </task>
  </activity>

  <definition xml:id="standard-form-of-a-quadratic-function">
    <statement>
      <p> Given the standard form of a quadratic function, <m>f(x)=ax^2+bx+c</m>, with real coefficients <m>a, b </m>, and <m> c </m>, the axis of symmetry is defined as <m> x=\frac {-b}{2a}</m> and has a vertex at the point <m> (\frac{-b}{2a},f(\frac{-b}{2a}))</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>

  <activity xml:id="activity-3">
